Ugandan Government Says Heritage Oil Tax Assessment $434 Million

-- B y   F r e d   O j a m b o
-- 
2011-09-22T09:32:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-22/ugandan-government-says-heritage-oil-tax-assessment-434-million.html
The Ugandan government’s assessment
of the tax owed following  Heritage Oil Plc (HOIL) ’s sale of its
interests in two oil blocks in the East African country totaled
$434 million, Energy Minister Irene Muloni said.  The government recovered the tax from  Tullow Oil Plc (TLW) , the
purchaser of Heritage’s interest in Block 1 and Block 3A,
Attorney General Peter Nyombi told reporters today in Kampala,
the capital.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Fred Ojambo in Kampala at 
 fojambo@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
